"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-27-Chinese-shooters-Huang-Yuting-and-Sheng-Lihao-win-first-gold-of-Paris-Olympics-in-10m-air-rifle-1vzRFAegEfu-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Huang Yuting (L) and Sheng Lihao of China win the 10-meter air rifle mixed team shooting gold medal at the 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris, July 27, 2024. /CFP  Huang Yuting and Sheng Lihao of China won the first gold medal at the 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris on Saturday after defeating Keum Ji-hyeon and Park Ha-jun of South Korea 16-12 in the 10-meter air rifle mixed team shooting final.  Alexandra Le and Islam Satpayev of Kazakhstan brought home the bronze medal after beating Maximilian Ulbrich and Anna Janssen of Germany 17-5 in the other match.  The gold medal match was tied 2-2 after the first two rounds and then the Chinese pair claimed the next two rounds to lead 6-2 before the South Korean coach called a timeout.  Huang and Sheng continued to expand their lead the match went on. They secured the match point with a 14-8 lead after the 11th round. Though Keum and Park cut their deficit to two points (14-12), the Chinese pair finished the competition in the 14th round to win their first Olympic gold.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"